 Thus, in order for us to model such systems, and to take into account strong
 light-matter couplings, the most natural approach is to consider the quantum
 subsystems and classical electromagnetic (EM) fields on an equal footing.
 This approach stands in contrast to most existing semiclassical approaches
 for spectroscopy, which treat the incoming field as an fixed external perturbat
