 coupling can be written as 
\begin_inset Formula $\widehat{\mu}E_{I}e^{-i\omega_{I}t}/2$
\end_inset

 for an incoming photon with amplitude 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{I}$
\end_inset

 and frequency 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{I}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\widehat{\mu}E_{S}e^{i\omega_{S}t}/2$
\end_inset

 for an outgoing photon with amplitude 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{S}$
\end_inset

 and frequency 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{S}$
\end_inset

.
 (The amplitude 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{S}$
\end_inset

 will be determined below.) Here 
\begin_inset Formula $\widehat{\mu}$
\end_inset

 is the dipole operator of the electronic system.
 According to second order perturbation theory within the Schr
